<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,906,1077]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,906,932]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Comments:</emphasis>
Only one individual was collected, presenting: (1) the ventral portion of all tibiae and femora black, (2) wings almost as long as twice the length of the femur III, with some black punctuations, (3) rounded fastigium, longer than wide, with a yellowish apex, (4) blackened fastigium of the vertex, with a black spot just above the fastigium tooth, (5) mirror almost circular, all borders convex.
</paragraph>
